```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User/Client
    participant S as SmartSearch
    participant D as Database Provider
    participant C as Cache Provider
    participant CB as Circuit Breaker
    participant HM as Health Monitor
    
    U->>S: Search Request (query, options)
    S->>HM: Check health status
    HM-->>S: Health status (cache/db availability)
    
    alt Cache is healthy and available
        S->>C: Search in cache
        alt Cache hit
            C-->>S: Return cached results
            S-->>U: Return results (strategy: cache)
        else Cache miss
            C-->>S: No results found
            S->>D: Search in database
            D-->>S: Return database results
            S->>C: Cache results
            S-->>U: Return results (strategy: cache-first)
        end
    else Cache unavailable/unhealthy
        S->>D: Search in database
        D-->>S: Return database results
        S-->>U: Return results (strategy: database)
    end
    
    Note over S, CB: Circuit breaker monitors failures
    Note over S, HM: Health monitor updates status periodically
```
